						               													<description>A game of Civil War trivia played across a map of the U.S. and C.S.A. with lead figures. It uses a mix of wargaming and trivia to reproduce the American Civil War.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players each have 3 armies. On a players turn they will roll the dice, march an army, and answer a question. As a bonus to answering a question correctly, an Active Move is earned. An incorrect answer always ends a players turn. Battles are fought when players end their turn with their armies in the same space as the other player. The game ends when one player holds 5 key positions in the West and Eastern theaters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Action Moves&amp;#10;a) Raise the Colors&amp;#10;b) Travel by Rail&amp;#10;c) Travel by Water&amp;#10;d) Draw a Travel Card&amp;#10;e) Parole an Army&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the Creators&amp;#10;Civil War Trivia Board Game was produced with the Civil War enthusiast in mind. Based upon actual personalities and events of the Civil War era, it stands as a unique concept of trivia and strategy. So...make yourself Comfortable, General, and prepare to meet the enemy...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
